{"parentUuid": "7274559a-8fdf-4d75-96a8-6c414ec2e97c", "isSidechain": true, "promptId": "6c3a0b22-aa71-4abe-86b8-7ed7f2e35c75", "agentId": "a975ce8c87ff99190", "type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "toolu_01Gadf67DdgDFM27QTYw2okb", "type": "tool_result", "content": "2:Here is a complete, standalone design and Rust skeleton for gha-isolated \u2014 a wrapper CLI around gha-outrunner that gives you unified, reliable, VM-preferring GitHub Actions runners across macOS, Linux, and GCE.\n12:\t\u2022\tWork the same way on a developer laptop and inside a GCE VM.\n15:\t\u2022\tLinux with KVM \u2192 libvirt backend (VMs)\n16:\t\u2022\tLinux / GCE (no strong KVM) \u2192 Docker + Sysbox (with strict limits)\n17:\t\u2022\tGCE \u2192 Same as Linux (run inside a GCE VM)\n23:\u251c\u2500\u2500 Backend Selection (Tart / libvirt / Docker+Sysbox)\n27:\u2514\u2500\u2500 Optional GCE helpers\n32:\t4\tEnsure prerequisites (gha-outrunner binary, Sysbox/Tart, etc.)\n37:KVM/Tart?\n46:Linux + /dev/kvm\n51:Linux / GCE\n53:docker + Sysbox\n161:    pub has_kvm: bool,\n179:    let has_kvm = std::path::Path::new(\"/dev/kvm\").exists();\n182:    Platform { os, arch, has_kvm, has_tart }\n191:    DockerSysbox,\n199:    if plat.os == \"linux\" && plat.has_kvm {\n203:        return Backend::DockerSysbox; // assume Sysbox is installed or will be\n284:On GCE: Create a Linux VM \u2192 cargo install gha-isolated (or copy binary) \u2192 run the same commands.\n291:\t4\tPrerequisite installation logic (install Sysbox/Tart automatically where possible)", "is_error": false}]}, "uuid": "dc81c83a-6754-4af0-9446-32fd1f1cf5b2", "timestamp": "2026-07-03T22:00:34.403Z", "sourceToolAssistantUUID": "7274559a-8fdf-4d75-96a8-6c414ec2e97c", "userType": "external", "entrypoint": "cli", "cwd": "/home/jleechan/projects/worktree_runner", "sessionId": "8ca589dd-8422-44b1-a543-52bd7b71f14b", "version": "2.1.198", "gitBranch": "fix/linux-runner-pre-job-hook", "slug": "velvet-wishing-cake"}
